![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/e57fb773-2473-4e8c-852f-7ee4d889b5f7/received_827416999409921.jpeg)

Nick Khan spoke at the SBJ World Congress of Sports and hinted at potential locations for WrestleMania 41 in 2025. While not yet ready to unveil the exact venue, Khan provided some insights that offer fans a glimpse into what to expect.

Khan indicated that WrestleMania 2025 is unlikely to take place in an outdoor stadium on the East coast, suggesting a departure from this years' locations. Additionally, he ruled out scheduling the event to coincide with the Final Four, indicating a desire to avoid overlapping with other major sporting events.

One city that has emerged as a potential candidate for WrestleMania 2025 is Las Vegas. Known for its vibrant entertainment scene and state-of-the-art venues, Las Vegas offers an enticing prospect for hosting WWE's flagship event.

While Khan's remarks provide some clues about WrestleMania's future, WWE enthusiasts will have to wait for official confirmation regarding the event's location. As speculation continues to swirl, Las Vegas remains a frontrunner among the cities under consideration.

Stay tuned for further updates as WWE's plans for WrestleMania 2025 unfold, and fans eagerly anticipate the grand spectacle that lies ahead.